data.enText: in favour of new ideas, modern methods and change

data.chText: 稳步的；逐步的；稳定发展的

data.enText: a progressive reduction in the size of the workforce

connected with the form of a verb (for example I am waiting or It is raining ) that is made from a part of be and the present participle. Progressive forms are used to express an action that continues for a period of time.

data.chText: 进步人士；开明人士；改革派
data.enText: a person who is in favour of new ideas, modern methods and change

data.chText: 改革派与保守派之间的政治斗争
data.enText: political battles between progressives and conservatives

tr: a person who favors a political philosophy of progress and reform and the protection of civil liberties
a tense of verbs used in describing action that is on-going
favoring or promoting reform (often by government action)
(of a card game or a dance) involving a series of sections for which the participants successively change place or relative position
(of taxes) adjusted so that the rate increases as the amount of income increases

value.def: Someone who is progressive or has progressive ideas has modern ideas about how things should be done, rather than traditional ones.

example.ex: ...a progressive businessman who had voted for Roosevelt in 1932 and 1936...
example.tran: 在1932年和1936年投票支持罗斯福的开明商人

example.ex: Willan was able to point to the progressive changes he had already introduced...
example.tran: 维兰能够找出他已经采用的一些革新。

example.ex: The children go to a progressive school.
example.tran: 这些孩子在一所先进的学校念书。

posc.def: A progressive is someone who is progressive.

example.ex: The Republicans were deeply split between progressives and conservatives.
example.tran: 共和党的革新派和保守派之间存在严重的分裂。

value.def: A progressive change happens gradually over a period of time.

example.ex: One prominent symptom of the disease is progressive loss of memory.
example.tran: 这种疾病的一个显著症状就是记忆逐渐丧失。

example.ex: ...the progressive development of a common foreign and security policy.
example.tran: 共同外交与安全政策的逐步发展

value.tran: （变化等）逐渐的，逐步发生的，逐步发展的

example.ex: The amount of grant the council received from the Government was progressively reduced.
example.tran: 这个委员会获得的政府津贴数额逐渐减少。

value.def: In grammar, progressive means the same as continuous.
